        "created_at": "2017-07-17T17:28:41.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-Grand_Cru_Cru\" data-username=\"TomHill\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/edb3f5/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> TomHill:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>\u2026another white refreshed w/ CO2. If they\u2019re going to monkey around w/ the acidity, do it w/ tartaric. not CO2.<br>\nTom</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Couldn\u2019t agree more. Seems to be becoming more and more common, unfortunately.</p>",
