        "created_at": "2017-07-17T17:34:38.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>It\u2019s certainly be done in this country as well for quite some time. I\u2019ve had many a riesling, for instance, that had a good dose of dissolved CO2 in it - whether left over from fermentation in stainless or added just before betting.</p>\n<p>When I worked for another winery, we always checked the level of CO2 in certain white varieties just before bottling, especially those that were fermented and aged in stainless, and \u2018adjusted\u2019 oftentimes.</p>\n<p>Cheers.</p>",
